<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2526] Assignment operators and copy constructors in c++ don&apos;t copy the __isset struct</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2526</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a thrift protocol that returns a list of items. The items have optional fields. Putting these items in a vector the optional fields are not sent to clients as the assignment operator does not copy the __isset struct.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Generated code:&lt;br/&gt;
Item::Item(const Item&amp;amp; other3) {&lt;br/&gt;
  id = other3.id;&lt;br/&gt;
  title = other3.title;&lt;br/&gt;
  itemclass = other3.itemclass;&lt;br/&gt;
  thumbnailurl = other3.thumbnailurl;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding _&lt;em&gt;isset = other3.&lt;/em&gt;_isset; fixes this issue.&lt;br/&gt;
Same for the assignment operator.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
